# SafeBirth Connect — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
SafeBirth Connect is an SMS-first maternal support coordination system for crisis settings.
- Backend: Java 17, Spring Boot 3.2.x, H2, Twilio SDK
- Mobile: Flutter, Riverpod 2.x, Dio, sqflite, go_router, Freezed
- Languages: Arabic + English (bilingual support)

## Code Style

### Java/Spring Boot
- Use Java 17 features: records, pattern matching, sealed classes
- Follow package structure: `com.safebirth.<feature>.<layer>`
- Use Lombok annotations: @Getter, @Setter, @Builder, @RequiredArgsConstructor
- All services should be @Transactional(readOnly = true) by default
- Use @Transactional for write operations
- Log at appropriate levels: INFO for business events, DEBUG for flow details, WARN for issues
- Phone numbers in logs should be masked for privacy

### Flutter/Dart
- Feature-first folder structure: `features/<feature>/data|domain|presentation`
- Use Riverpod for state management with code generation
- Use Freezed for immutable data classes
- Use go_router for navigation
- All user-facing strings must use localization (AppLocalizations)
- Support RTL layouts for Arabic

## Naming Conventions

### Java
- Classes: PascalCase (MotherService, HelpRequest)
- Methods/Variables: camelCase (findByPhone, phoneNumber)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (MAX_RETRIES)
- Packages: lowercase (com.safebirth.domain.mother)

### Dart
- Classes: PascalCase (DashboardScreen, CaseModel)
- Files: snake_case (dashboard_screen.dart)
- Variables/Functions: camelCase (fetchCases, isLoading)
- Constants: lowerCamelCase or UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

## SMS Commands Reference

| Action | English | Arabic |
|--------|---------|--------|
| Register Mother | `REG MOTHER [camp] [zone]` | `تسجيل ام [مخيم] [منطقة]` |
| Register Volunteer | `REG VOLUNTEER [camp] [zones]` | `تسجيل متطوع [مخيم] [مناطق]` |
| Emergency | `EMERGENCY` / `SOS` | `طوارئ` |
| Support | `SUPPORT` | `مساعدة` |
| Accept Case | `ACCEPT HR-xxxx` | `قبول xxxx` |
| Complete Case | `COMPLETE HR-xxxx` | `انهاء xxxx` |
| Available | `AVAILABLE` | `متاح` |
| Busy | `BUSY` | `مشغول` |

## Error Handling

### Backend
- Use GlobalExceptionHandler for REST exceptions
- Custom exceptions: SmsDeliveryException, ResourceNotFoundException
- Always return meaningful error messages
- Never expose stack traces in production

### Flutter
- Use sealed classes for API exceptions
- Handle offline scenarios gracefully
- Show user-friendly error messages
- Implement retry logic for network failures

## Testing Guidelines

### Backend
- Unit tests for services with mocked dependencies
- Integration tests for controllers with MockMvc
- Test SMS parsing for both Arabic and English
- Test matching algorithm with various scenarios

### Flutter
- Widget tests for UI components
- Unit tests for providers and services
- Integration tests for critical flows

## Planning Protocol

Before implementing new features:
1. Check if a plan exists in `plans/` directory
2. Update PROGRESS.md status to "In Progress"
3. Follow the phase plan step by step
4. Update PROGRESS.md to "Completed" when done
5. Create/update tests as specified

## Security Notes (POC)

- No authentication implemented for POC
- Phone number used as identifier
- CORS is wide open for development
- Twilio credentials via environment variables
- H2 database for simplicity (use PostgreSQL in production)

## File Structure

```
safebirthconnect/
├── backend/                     # Spring Boot backend
│   └── src/main/java/com/safebirth/
│       ├── config/              # Configuration classes
│       ├── sms/                 # SMS handling
│       ├── domain/              # Business entities
│       ├── matching/            # Volunteer matching
│       ├── api/                 # REST controllers
│       └── exception/           # Exception handling
├── mobile/                      # Flutter app
│   └── lib/
│       ├── core/                # Core utilities
│       ├── features/            # Feature modules
│       └── shared/              # Shared widgets
├── plans/                       # Phase plans
└── .cursor/rules                # This file
```
